SIMPLE: half-moon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Half-moon
<hw>Half"-moon`</hw> <pr>(-m⟦oomac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The moon at the quarters, when half its disk appears
illuminated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The shape of a half-moon; a crescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>See how in warlike muster they appear,⟦br⟧
In rhombs, and wedges, and <qex>half-moons</qex>, and wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>An outwork composed of two faces,
forming a salient angle whose gorge resembles a half-moon; -- now called
a <altname>ravelin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A marine, sparoid, food fish of
California (<spn>Caesiosoma Californiense</spn>). The body is ovate,
blackish above, blue or gray below. Called also
<altname>medialuna</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Half nelson</ent>⟦br⟧
